            <h2><strong>What's a Fossil?</strong></h2>
            <p>Fossils are any traces of ancient life such as remains, traces or imprints of organisms that has been preserved by natural processes from some geologic past.  The examination and interpretation of fossils is an area of geological study called Paleontology.   Paleontologists utilize fossils in various ways although they are mainly used as; an aid in geologic mapping and stratigraphic correlation, as indicators of past depositional environments and as a representation of organic evolution and indicators of geologic time.</p>
          </div>
            
          </br>  
